{meta: title The Place Where I Worship}
{meta: artist R.W. Hammonds}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Oh the place where I worship is the wide open spaces
[F]Built by the hand of the [C]Lord
Where the trees of the forest are like pipes of an organ
[D7]And the breeze plays an amen [G7]chord
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[C]All the stars are the candles and they light up the mountains
[F]Mountains are altars of [C]God
Oh the place where I worship is the wide open spaces
[D7]Built by the [G7]hand of the [C]Lord
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
There’s a [F]carpet of green and a sky [C]blue roof above
[D7]And I’m welcome there along [G7]with the one I love
[C]In your heart take a good look if you follow the good book
[F]And you’re sure to find your [C]reward
Oh the place where I worship is the wide open spaces
[D7]Built by the [G7]hand of the [C]Lord
{end_of_verse}

